9:
It seems that word of my previous
lecture reached all the way to the
Farlands, and I've received an
invitation directly from one of the
noble families.
12:
I'm part of the Academy too now, so
I also got one!
19:
That's right! Everyone figured out
what happened during my previous
lecture, and now Rei's abilities are
receiving the recognition they
deserve.
22:
Her lectures are even far more
popular than mine!
27: You seem pretty happy about that.
32:
...Can I see that invitation for a
moment?
38:
I'm not terribly familiar with the
Farlands so I'm just going with what
I've heard, but...
41:
The Sextan family is apparently... full
of oddballs.
47:
The Sextans have a good
relationship with Palpebra and have
also had a long, positive relationship
with the Academy.
51:
But on a more personal level... You
two are still new around here, so it'll
be harder for the Academy to have
your back out there...
54:
Gross, politics? Even in a different
world, all that stuff is still awful.
57:
...Perhaps we should decline the
invitation after all?
60: Say what? We've gotta go, Ciph.
63:
You were the one complaining a
moment ago!
66:
If they start giving off bad vibes we'll
grab their research findings and
split! We'll be Crimson Blades for a
day!
69:
Honestly, that sounds rather fun...
But we can't cause trouble for the
Academy.
75: Marina would be happy to have you.
79:
As a professor at Voluntas
Academy, I can't let you do that...
82:
But, seriously. You don't need to go if
you don't want to.
86:
No, we will go. I must seize this rare
opportunity to pay the Academy
back for everything they've given
me!
89:
We'll be fiiine. The Crimson Blades
have got nothing on my "Scourge of
the Seas" sister here.
116:
But they gave me this. Or rather, I...
borrowed it?
121:
Is this... a Sextan paper on
cursebreaking? Wait... this isn't
published, either!
134:
I can't say why... I'm not sure,
exactly...
137:
She stood in front of everyone and
gave them the Cipher Special. The
lecture went about as well as you'd
expect.
140:
They begged us to leave, saying
they'd do anything for us if we just
went home. The nerve!
143:
We didn't meet a single dignitary or
representative or anything, either!
147:
Couette had a similar experience.
The unknown frightens them.
150:
Don't forget we're in Palpebra, home
of the Kaleidoscope. People here are
much more used to folks like you
than the Sextans.
159:
They could have simply turned you
away empty-handed, though.
Maybe this was their way of... saying
sorry?
163:
Perhaps they had a reason for
turning you away in such a hurry?
For example, I'm curious why you
didn't meet any dignitaries.
167:
What's with all the noise?
Oh, Cipher. You're back early.
176: Hello, Rei. What's this book about?
179:
It's, like... How to expand force fields,
or something?
182:
A practical demonstration seems to
be in order. Don't keep us waiting,
Cipher!
187:
A-all right, then! Fine! But in return,
you're going to help!
194:
Rei. You're much more interested in
research than I, aren't you?
197: What're you going on about now?
200:
Well, you spend a lot of time
studying things unrelated to
cursebreaking. You're popular with
students, as well.
203:
Yeah, probably 'cause studying
theory sucks. What's your point?
209:
Why don't you leave cursebreaking
to me, and you can study what you
care about?
212:
All this living large is really getting to
your head, huh?
218:
Stop worrying about me like I'm
useless. I'm not giving up on life,
frozen in some cave anymore, right?
224:
I want to become a teacher. A real
one, going through all the hoops.
226:
But I'll also keep studying
cursebreaking. It's pretty fun,
anyway.
228:
Up until pretty recently I couldn't
even dream of that. But I've got a
goal now.
230:
So again. I'm fine, Ciph. We can be
true to ourselves and still be the
best teachers around.
238:
But like, what about you? Do you
have a dream, or whatever?
241: Hmm, a dream? Let me think...
